 Clinical practice in the reported trials was considered not contemporary.

 In the modern practice of combination endoscopic treatment and maximal acid suppression, the use of routine second look endoscopy cannot be recommended as the NNT to prevent further bleeding would likely be higher.

 A policy of routine second look endoscopy is generally not recommended as suggested by an International Consensus Group [ 8 ].

 Second look endoscopy in those at high risk of further bleeding is however a logical approach.

 The NNT to prevent further bleeding diminishes as risk of further bleeding increases.

 For instance, an ulcer > 2 cm in size with Forrest I or Forrest II a bleeding would be associated with a re-bleeding risk of 15-20% even with high dose PPI infusion.

